# The Internet Theory
# What exactly is the internet ?

# It is a long piece of wire, and the wire connects different computers to
# each other.

# eg, one computer in seattle, and other one in london, now, some of
these computer attached to the internet have special jobs

# they have to be online 24/7 and ready serve all the data and files that we
# request when we try to access internet. These are called Servers.

# they serve us all the data and file we need to be able to access and interact
# with certain websites. These computers are called Servers and any computer
# that the users use to access the internet is called the client.

# A webserver is like a giant library that is open 4/7 and request for any website
# we want to access, and it will serve us with all the files and data we need to view whatever website we want.


# when we type a url link, browser sends it to ISP (internet service provider), the message
# we send to isp, it will route to a DNS server (Domain Name System server), and the DNS server is
# essentially just a souped us phone book, when we make the request through the browser, the
# DNS server will look up the address of the website that we're trying to access.
# Every single computer connected to the internet have an IP address, it's like a postal code for your computer
# SO when people need to send or receive files from the internet, each computer can be
# located and contacted using their unique IP address, once DNS server finds the IP address, it sends it back to the
# browser via the ISP. Then we can make a direct request to the address servers.
 
